parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to surge forward unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels hard to press
causing the vehicle to lunge forward or accelerate rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the accelerator pedal to stick, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels hard to press
causing the vehicle to lunge forward or accelerate rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight and taillight sockets can cause the lights to malfunction or not function at all, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals and brake lights can cause confusion and increase the risk of accidents, especially when turning or stopping.
symptoms: Turn signals not visible during the day or hard to see at night
brake lights failing on one or both sides
and erratic behavior of turn signals and windshield wipers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system issues can cause various problems, including malfunctioning lights, erratic behavior of accessories, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: erratic behavior of turn signals and windshield wipers
and malfunctioning accessories like the tape player.
